ðŸ”¹ Categories of SQL Keywords
âœ… 1. Data Query Keywords (DQL)
Used to retrieve data from a database.

Keyword	Purpose
SELECT	Fetch data from a table
FROM	Specify the table(s) to query
WHERE	Filter rows based on condition
GROUP BY	Group rows sharing values
ORDER BY	Sort result set
HAVING	Filter groups (after GROUP BY)
DISTINCT	Remove duplicates
LIMIT	Limit the number of rows

âœ… 2. Data Definition Keywords (DDL)
Used to define and modify structure of database objects like tables.

Keyword	Purpose
CREATE	Create tables, databases, etc.
DROP	Delete tables, databases, etc.
ALTER	Modify existing table structure
RENAME	Rename a table or column
TRUNCATE	Remove all rows, reset auto-increment

âœ… 3. Data Manipulation Keywords (DML)
Used to manipulate data within tables.

Keyword	Purpose
INSERT	Add new rows to a table
UPDATE	Modify existing rows
DELETE	Delete rows from a table
VALUES	Provide data values
SET	Set column values in UPDATE

âœ… 4. Data Control Keywords (DCL)
Used to control access to data.

Keyword	Purpose
GRANT	Give user privileges
REVOKE	Remove user privileges

âœ… 5. Transaction Control Keywords (TCL)
Used to manage transactions and changes.

Keyword	Purpose
COMMIT	Save all changes
ROLLBACK	Undo changes since last commit
SAVEPOINT	Set a save point for partial rollback
BEGIN	Start a transaction

âœ… 6. Joins and Subqueries
Keyword	Purpose
JOIN	Combine rows from multiple tables
INNER JOIN	Return matching rows
LEFT JOIN	All rows from left, matched from right
RIGHT JOIN	All rows from right, matched from left
FULL JOIN	All rows from both tables
ON	Specify join condition
IN	Match value in list or subquery
EXISTS	Check existence of subquery rows
ANY, ALL	Compare to any/all values in subquery

âœ… 7. Constraints and Definitions
Keyword	Purpose
PRIMARY KEY	Unique identifier
FOREIGN KEY	Link to primary key of another table
NOT NULL	Prevent null values
UNIQUE	Ensure all values are unique
CHECK	Ensure condition is met
DEFAULT	Set default value
AUTO_INCREMENT	Automatically increment numeric value

âœ… 8. Miscellaneous Keywords
Keyword	Purpose
AS	Rename a column or table alias
IS NULL	Check if value is NULL
BETWEEN	Match a range of values
LIKE	Match a pattern
CASE	If-else logic in SQL
CAST, CONVERT	Change data type
UNION	Combine results from two queries
ALL, ANY, SOME	Quantifiers

